### .gitignore
#
# Defines which files are to be allowed as a part of the project. Instead of
# denying specific folder and/or files, this file first denies EVERYTHING, and
# then specifically allows for wanted files and file types with an exclamation
# mark ! at the start of each allowed pattern.
#

## Disallow everything.

*

## Allow specific files.

!.gitignore

!.gitattributes

!README.md

!LICENSE

!CONTRIBUTING.md

!CHANGELOG.md

!tauthesis.cls

!titlepage.tex

!preamble.tex

!set-pdf-version.tex

!main.tex

## Allow file types in subdirectories.

!tex/
!tex/*.tex

!code/
!code/*.c
!code/*.cc
!code/*.cpp
!code/*.h
!code/*.hh
!code/*.jl
!code/*.js
!code/*.json
!code/*.m
!code/*.py
!code/*.rs
!code/*.toml
!code/*.ts
!code/*.yaml
!code/*.yml
!code/*.zig

!figures/
!figures/**/*.eps
!figures/**/*.jpg
!figures/**/*.pdf
!figures/**/*.png

# Disallow PDF figures automatically generated from EPS via epstopdf. Only the
# original EPS figures should be in the repository to avoid repetition.

figures/**/*-eps-converted-to.pdf
